
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `aplaymidi` baraye pakhsh file-haye MIDI az tarigh terminal estefade mishavad. MIDI yek format baraye music electronic ast.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `aplaymidi -l`  --> 🎤 List kardane port-haye MIDI mojud dar system.
    🔹 `aplaymidi -p <port>`  --> 📍 Entkhab kardane port MIDI baraye pakhsh. Masalan: `aplaymidi -p 20:0 file.mid`
    🔹 `aplaymidi --port=<port>` --> 📍 Digar shekl entekhab port MIDI.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ aplaymidi file.mid

    🔹 Pakhsh file MIDI ba estefade az port pishfarz.

    $ aplaymidi -p 20:0 file.mid

    🔹 Pakhsh file MIDI az port shomare 20:0.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ aplaymidi -l

    🔹 List kardane hameye device-haye MIDI ke mishe estefade kard baraye pakhsh file MIDI. Shoma mitoonid az in list estefade konid ta port sahih ra baraye gozine `-p` entekhab konid.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `aplaymidi` command is used to play MIDI files through the terminal. MIDI is a format for electronic music.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `aplaymidi -l`  --> 🎤 List available MIDI ports on the system.
    🔹 `aplaymidi -p <port>`  --> 📍 Select the MIDI port to use for playback.  For example: `aplaymidi -p 20:0 file.mid`
    🔹 `aplaymidi --port=<port>` --> 📍 Another way to select the MIDI port.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ aplaymidi file.mid

    🔹 Play the MIDI file using the default MIDI port.

    $ aplaymidi -p 20:0 file.mid

    🔹 Play the MIDI file using MIDI port number 20:0.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ aplaymidi -l

    🔹 Lists all MIDI devices available for playback. You can use this list to determine the correct port to use with the `-p` option.
